reviews.review: I like Knives out movie because it's was amazing movie I love it so much and it's was a great movie I give this movie a 100 percent review
Loved it. A movie for everyone.

A total delight. Each actor is having a blast playing their role, and they get so many great chances, from iconic lines, to memorable reaction shots. Rian Johnson deftly tells a whodunnit, (or does he?), mixed in with the trappings of class, and the value of goodness. There are minor points where you truly wonder what the object of the price is, and where the film is driving, but it has an ending that more than makes up for it.

I honestly think this is the best movie of the year. An incredible homage to the genre, this whodunnit has everything an audience would love. Unexpectedly funny, and a perfect film to come out on Thanksgiving. I was lucky enough to get early screener tickets but I enjoyed it so much I think I may actually bring my family to see it again. Each cast member shines in their respective roles but Ana definitely steals the show. Definitely a must see! You'll never see a donut in the same way
Each of the cast of characters was well suited to their role. Daniel Craig was excellent.  It was a good who done it with a twist.
A total Who Done It in the genre of Agatha Christie.  Good twists and turns with a nice wait-for-it ending. Well done.

Supremely silly and yet tightly wound and snappily written. The kind of script with way more comedy than the audience can catch in a single viewing... and by the same token, sweeter and more good-hearted than expected.

Sensational movie! They need to make more movies like this. Great murder mystery film with lots of twists and turns with rich characters. Everyone did an outstanding job. Storyline was intriguing. Big thumbs up!

I can't recommend Knives Out enough! It's extremely well-crafted (and well-acted) with plenty of twists and turns. If you like murder mysteries and/or suspense, it's an absolute must-see! Definitely one of my favorite movies of the year so far.

A fun film with great performances from the entire cast, terrific set pieces that provide the appropriate atmospherics, and a well-paced narrative that never seemed to drag or wander off track. It does what it's supposed to do: keep the audience engaged and provide an enjoyable experience at the cinema.
